radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases are clear. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. Mild-to-moderate amount of ascites noted in the perihepatic and perisplenic regions. Focal dense material adjacent to a speck of air likely represents an appendicolith. Distended tubular structure containing appendicolith measuring 14 mm, likely representing a fluid-filled appendix. Normal uterus and adnexae. Mild-to-moderate amount of free fluid in the deep pelvis.
